description: The humor in this joke lies in the literal interpretation of an idiom, leading to a visually comic situation.
title: Eyebrow Escapade
n_1: In their home, Emily meticulously adjusts her eyebrows, John watches curiously.
n_2: Emily carefully draws her eyebrows higher, John observes with a hint of humor.
n_3: John comments on her high eyebrows. Emily, surprised, turns to him.
n_4: The couple shares a light-hearted moment, laughing together.
c1_1: “You're really raising the bar with those eyebrows.”
c1_2: “Are they satellite antennas for better reception?”
c2_2: “Funny, I thought you'd appreciate the art.”
c1_3: “I think they're a bit too high.”
c2_4: “Guess I'm an open book with these brows!”
